ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule, DA leader John Steenhuisen and UDM leader Bantu Holomisa reflect on the life of Nelson Mandela and the inequalities that persist in South Africa. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule, DA leader John Steenhuisen and UDM leader Bantu Holomisa have reflected on the life of Nelson Mandela and the inequalities that persist in South Africa. Steenhuisen highlighted that poverty is the number one killer in the country and is responsible for many more deaths than COVID-19. While Holomisa says Mandela would not be proud of today's ANC. He says the party has turned from struggle heroes into looters. READ:Â Mandela was the greatest leader of our time: Ramaphosa The leaders were reflecting on United Nations Secretary-General Antonio Guterres's 18th Nelson Mandela Annual Lecture. This year's lecture is themed, 'Tackling Inequality: A New Social Contract For a New Era'. Watch the full interview above.